The digital safe has been designed to be accessible to as many people as possible. It is quick and intuitive to use, even for people who are not familiar with digital technology. Creating an account does not require a phone number or email address. The tool is translated into several languages and our mobile application allows it to be accessible from a computer or a phone.
a complete and secured storage tool
The digital safe allows you to keep digital copies of administrative files, to save events with an SMS reminder system, to keep a contact list and useful notes.
A complete and secured storage tool
From this interface, a professional can find all the safes linked to his structure, feed them and check on the shared information. They can also create a safe at the request of a supported person.
An interface for social support workers
The tool that facilitates access to rights for vulnerable populations and social support

The section called "Mes Relais" allows the safe to be linked to the support organizations attended by the beneficiary. Each of the information stored in the safe can then be shared or not with the professionals who support him/her. At any time, the beneficiary can choose to break this link.
The digital safe allows to fight against the lacks of progress due to the loss of information. The integration process is thus made smoother.
The digital safe is a tool that encourages exchanges between the person being supported and the organization. It allows the beneficiary to become an actor in the progression of his own path.
A facilitated exchange of information with caregivers
The digital safe is an ethical and secured tool. It is compliant with the RGPD law. The protection of our users' personal data is our top priority.

Digital workshops are part of the overall support of the beneficiaries, and meet a need for training in the use of digital technology, to facilitate their social and professional integration.
A support to improve integration pathways

Our workshops contain a theoretical and practical dimension to facilitate the assimilation of information. The sessions are built using a "gamified" methodology that facilitates attention and improves attractiveness. We pay particular attention to the immediate practical application of the proposed training.

Contents and presentation materials are prepared in advance by the Reconnect team, according to the themes identified by the professionals of the structure, and to the needs of the public. Reconnect's approach to digital mediation is to continuously adapt to the levels and needs of beneficiaries.
Evolving contents according to feedback from the field

Beneficiaries are asked to measure their progress and to evaluate the training, in order to develop our content. This approach is coupled with a monitoring of new developments in the digital inclusion sector to ensure that our content best meets the needs of the beneficiaries.
Evolving contents according to feedback from the field

"An online Storage and Sharing platform to boost social care"
Coping with extreme poverty and high mobility, the homeless are facing the issue of keeping their documents safe, which is essential in order to obtain social benefits.

Reconnect allows to safely store the copy of all essential documents, scanned or pictured, as well as contacts, appointments and memos. In case of losing the original documents, the consequences are thus limited.
The Reconnect Centres support the users in the creation and management of their Reconnect account.
The creation of a Reconnect account is freely offered to people living in extreme poverty in the Reconnect Centres.
Reconnect adapts to the wants and needs of its users, who are free to choose whether or not they want to share their data and documents with social workers.

The user can access his account without being affiliated to a Reconnect Centre. If he decides to quit his centre, he will be able to benefit from his Reconnect devices for an unlimited period of time. If he chooses a new centre, he will again be able to share his essential documents.

Reconnect is a device meant to last, which adapts to the social background of everyone. By using Reconnect, social actors can accompany people living in extreme poverty toward the autonomous usage of a digital tool.

Storing and sharing information and documents online.
Reminder of memos and events via SMS.
Simulation of the social rights for which the users are eligible and automatic creation of an administrative record from the available documents in the safe.
An answer for the needs of homeless people
A service offered to people living in extremely precarious conditions
1.  Open an account in a Reconnect Centre
2.  Back up your most important files
3.  Share your key documents to speed up your administrative and social procedures
4.  Get an easier access to your social rights

Reconnect Centres are social care structures. They help their beneficiaries create and use a Reconnect account. They facilitate the secured sharing of key information and documents between beneficiaries and their social advisers to boost administrative and social procedures.

Reconnect is a project led by Groupe SOS Solidarity. With 2500 employees and 106 care facilities specialized in the sectors of addiction conselling, socially-cohesive housing, and services for handicapped people, Groupe SOS Solidarity’s involvement towards social innovation is a strong asset for the development of Reconnect. For the prevailing interest of its end-users, Reconnect aims at being available in as many social care services as possible, regardless of their size or their location.
Digital technology for inclusion and social action
The tool that facilitates access to rights for vulnerable populations and social support
The business tool that ensures the continuity of social integration pathways
"Relais Reconnect" are the social structures that use the Reconnect solutions and support users in the creation and use of their digital safe.
The interfaces of our tools have been designed to be pleasant and intuitive to use, even for people who are not familiar with digital technology.
Our solutions are designed in partnership with social action organizations in order to best meet the needs of the sector. The changes we make on a daily basis are based on feedback from our users.
Our professional users are accompanied in the handling and use of our solutions thanks to a complete training and a dedicated online support.
The security and protection of our users' personal data are our top priority. Our tools are designed and developed in an ethical and secured way. They are RGPD compliant.
All our solutions work with a solidarity rate in order to offer a service accessible to all social structures.
Reconnect is a non-profit association of which mission is to facilitate the progression of social integration while simplifying the support of professionals.
We believe that social action and digital benefit from working more together in order to enable the social inclusion of vulnerable populations.
Since 2015, we have been committed to beneficiaries and social action professionals, creating solutions to meet their needs.
The solution to meet the challenges of the digital divide
